# Power BI Dashboard – Safety Signal Monitoring

This dashboard represents the visualization and monitoring layer of the
**AI-Assisted Dashboard for Safety Signal Monitoring** project.

The dashboard is designed to provide a high-level overview of drug safety
patterns and support exploratory safety signal monitoring.

---

## Dashboard Objectives

- Provide a consolidated view of drug safety data
- Compare safety patterns across prescription types (Rx vs OTC)
- Highlight availability of adverse effect information
- Assess pregnancy risk category distribution
- Support interactive and exploratory analysis

---

## Key Dashboard Components

### KPI Cards
- Total number of drugs in the dataset
- Count of prescription (Rx) drugs
- Count of over-the-counter (OTC) drugs

These KPIs provide immediate context about the dataset composition.

---

### Adverse Effect Availability by Prescription Type
This clustered column chart compares the number of drug records with reported
adverse effects across Rx and OTC categories.

Differences between KPI counts and chart values reflect missing or unreported
adverse effect information, which is common in real-world safety datasets.

---

### Average User Rating by Prescription Type
This visualization compares average user-reported ratings across prescription
categories. Ratings are used as a perception-based metric and not as a clinical
safety indicator.

---

### Pregnancy Risk Category Distribution
A donut chart visualizes the distribution of drugs across pregnancy risk
categories, supporting regulatory and safety-focused analysis.

---

## Interactivity
Slicers are provided for:
- Prescription Type
- Pregnancy Category

These filters enable focused and interactive exploration of safety patterns.

---

## AI-Assisted Insights
AI-assisted tools were used to help summarize observed visual patterns and
support interpretation of dashboard trends. Final conclusions and safety
interpretations remain analyst-driven.

---

## Note on Data
The Power BI dashboard is shared as screenshots due to file size constraints.
Raw datasets are excluded from the repository due to size and data handling
considerations.
